name: Icarus
description: Digital collage (2400x3200px) Icarus is an extremely eccentric asteroid, approximately 1.4 km (0.87 mi) in diameter. It is a near-Earth object of the Apollo group and the lowest numbered potentially hazardous asteroid. This minor planet was named after Icarus, son of Daedalus (also see 1864 Daedalus) from Greek mythology
